      $method = $this->router->method;\n        if ($class == 'auth') {\n            if (in_array($method, array('do_login', 'do_logout', 'view_change_password', 'save_change_pass_html'))) {\n                return;\n            }\n        }\n\n        $sess_id = $this->session->userdata('id');\n        $sess_perfil = $this->session->userdata('perfil');\n        $sess_needs_reset = $this->session->userdata('needs_reset');\n\n        if (empty($sess_id)) {\n            $all = $this->session->all_userdata();\n            $this->view_login('Ud no tiene permiso para ver este mÃ³dulo');\n            $this->output->_display();\n            exit();\n        }\n\n        if ($sess_needs_reset == true && ! in_array($method, array('view_login', 'do_login', 'view_change_password', 'save_change_pass_html'))) {\n            $base_path = reduce_double_slashes($this->config->base_url() . index_page());\n            $this->session->set_flashdata('msg', 'Debe cambiar su clave antes de poder ingresar.');\n            redirect($base_path . '/cpan/auth/view_change_password');\n        }\n    }\n```\n\nThat method tries to read data from the session, but I keep running into the error \n\n> Unable to locate the specified class: Session.php\n\nI've tried \n- changing the hook type from `pre_controller` to `post_controller_constructor` and `post_controller`, \n- using a direct `$CI` reference in the method, \n- loading the library directly in the method and not with autoload\n\nbut I always get the same error. Could it be that the `load_class` method in `Common.php` is not checking inside the Session subdirectory?\n","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/bcit-ci/CodeIgniter/issues/4707/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/bcit-ci/CodeIgniter/issues/4707/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed"}},"event":"cross-referenced"}]